This paper is about human pose estimation using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new design choice for skip connections within the network, which involves per-channel learnable parameters, indicating a focus on improving the efficiency and accuracy of the model, which aligns with the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of the HourGlass and U-Net architectures, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) applications.
